1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:04,340
Episode 26

2
00:00:27,140 --> 00:00:29,780
I'm going to the police station to provide a witness statement.

3
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,830
I'll contact you when I'm done. Let's have a meal together, I have something to speak to you about.

4
00:00:34,830 --> 00:00:37,890
I wonder what has happened?

5
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:40,540
Mr. Tone-Deaf

6
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:47,590
Breaking news. Gyeonggi Western District Police, regarding the body of Mr. Yun,
[ Mr. Jang of Sinyeong Philharmonic, Arrested Without Warrant on Suspicion of Murder ]

7
00:00:47,590 --> 00:00:50,510
discovered at Sinyeong Philharmonic, the pianist of Sinyeong Philharmonic,

8
00:00:50,510 --> 00:00:53,960
Mr. Jang was arrested without warrant and is currently under investigation.

9
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:56,380
On the 27th, near Myeongnyun-dong in Seoul...

10
00:00:56,380 --> 00:00:58,800
Oh my God.
... Mr. Yun  died...

11
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:02,080
the police discovered CCTV footage which shows Mr. Jang fighting with him

12
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:05,690
- What is going on?
and found Mr. Jang to be a suspect.

13
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:09,280
Jang Yun killed someone?

14
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:13,640
Hey, you be careful, don't you dare spit out whatever you want.

15
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:16,340
Nothing is certain, after all.

16
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:19,170
Body of Mr. Yun Discovered at Sinyeong Philharmonic, Pianist Mr. Jang, Arrested Without Warrant on Suspicion of Murder

17
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:35,640
Jenny

18
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:11,330
What a sight. I tried to stop you, but you insisted on going around stirring things up.

19
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:15,910
You came just to say that to me?

20
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:20,140
Did you do it?

21
00:02:20,820 --> 00:02:27,020
To be honest, I sometimes thought about it, but it's not me. When will I be released?

22
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:33,160
You can only be held in custody for 48 hours. Without evidence, they cannot prosecute you.

23
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:36,470
How dare they arrest you because of just CCTV footage? Without any evidence?

24
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:42,060
Ah, two days. I can't wait that long, I have to get out now.

25
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:47,720
I found out who took Yun Yeong Gil's personal belongings.

26
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:51,220
- Who was it?
- Nam Ju Wan.

27
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:54,200
- The conductor?
- Yes.

28
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:59,320
He may have killed Ian. And Professor Kang of Sinyeong Music College is involved, too.

29
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:02,220
I cannot stay here, please get me out immediately.

30
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:08,110
Father, you got into Sinyeong Philharmonic with a purpose, too. This is the time to make your move.

31
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:10,540
I know that.

32
00:03:12,130 --> 00:03:14,870
And, Father?

33
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:16,750
What?

34
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:21,590
- Please explain this well.
- To who?

35
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:24,480
To Hong Yi Yeong.

36
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:28,000
She must have been so shocked, but I have no way to contact her.

37
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,270
Gi Sang is outside, isn't he? He will know her contact information.

38
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:34,030
What do you want me to tell her?

39
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:36,370
Just...

40
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:42,590
to not take any rash actions, and to be careful.

41
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:46,390
That I will be released soon.

42
00:03:46,390 --> 00:03:51,060
Won't she come visit you? You can tell her yourself.

43
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:17,930
Did you bring it? Where did you find that?

44
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:20,550
Yun Yeong Gil's storage locker.

45
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:27,430
That's where he hid it? What a simpleton. Anyway, give it to me now.

46
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,810
Did you smile? Why?

47
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:34,780
Because you didn't think of such a simple answer.

48
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:40,460
In times like this, I really wonder how you managed to remain in your position for so long.

49
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:42,960
You must have been lucky all this time.

50
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:48,600
Hey, you're speaking too carelessly. I did everything you wanted me to.

51
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:53,090
I even turned the suspicion away from you, so hand it over.

52
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:57,380
- You must help me some more.
- Haven't I been helping you all along?

53
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:02,360
- How can I possibly help you more?
- I want to remain at Sinyeong Philharmonic.

54
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:08,370
That's nothing to you. After all, you even killed someone.

55
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:11,120
Are you finished?

56
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:19,910
Did you have Yun Yeong Gil take care of the car after the accident last year?

57
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:24,180
- What about it?
- Oh Professor, you sure are sloppy.

58
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:29,940
Yun Yeong Gil asked me to tell you this, that humans are not the only things that can see.

59
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:35,550
What does that mean? Yun Yeong Gil really said that?

60
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:37,830
When?

61
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:50,150
So you really did kill him.

62
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:55,970
What are you saying? Jang Yun killed Yun Yeong Gil.

63
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:06,360
What, you haven't left work yet?

64
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:09,310
Have you seen the news?

65
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:17,530
You don't seem bothered at all, Conductor.

66
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:25,970
- Do I really look not bothered?
- Maybe you're relieved?

67
00:06:25,970 --> 00:06:31,940
You seem pretty happy. Someone else was the murderer but Yun was arrested instead.

68
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:35,540
It's the police's job to discover the murderer.

69
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:39,960
I am certain that you met with Yeong Gil on that day.

70
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:43,350
Because I definitely saw those flowers.

71
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:48,380
Where were you right before the performance?

72
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:51,640
That was when you met with Yun Yeong Gil, isn't it?

73
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:55,290
No, I did not.

74
00:06:55,290 --> 00:07:02,310
I can't believe you. You lied to me so many times, don't you remember?

75
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:08,070
You pretended to be interested in me, but the truth is, you were watching me.

76
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:11,630
Because you were afraid that I would remember that day from a year ago.

77
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:19,210
That I would remember you killing Ian. Isn't that true?

78
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:27,530
What would you have done if I remembered? Were you going to kill me, too?

79
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:33,350
Like you killed Kim Ian? Like you killed Yun Yeong Gil?

80
00:07:33,350 --> 00:07:36,410
Whatever I say, you wouldn't believe me anyway.

81
00:07:36,410 --> 00:07:42,690
How can I believe you? You deceived me and my aunt and uncle, too.

82
00:07:42,690 --> 00:07:47,370
You laughed and ate at their home like you'd become family or something.

83
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:52,100
And you made Yun take the blame for everything, when he is completely innocent.

84
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,170
How can you do that?

85
00:07:57,230 --> 00:07:59,730
Go turn yourself in.

86
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:04,210
Right now, turn yourself in.

87
00:08:04,210 --> 00:08:07,640
You are the one who did all these things.

88
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:12,310
Liar.

89
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:15,830
Murderer.

90
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:19,520
Please let Yun be released.

91
00:08:25,590 --> 00:08:32,860
I understand that you want to lock me up instead of Jang Yun, but I am not the one who did those things.

92
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:56,740
Hello, my name is Hong Yi Yeong.

93
00:08:56,740 --> 00:09:01,080
Yes, have a seat.

94
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:13,380
I apologize for showing up suddenly.

95
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,600
I heard that you were helping a friend of mine,

96
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:19,500
so I took it upon myself to ask for your phone number and place of work.

97
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,500
Eun Ju, you mean?

98
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:27,130
But what is it that you want to tell me?

99
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:34,330
I wanted to tell you what I know about Kim Ian's incident last year.

100
00:09:34,330 --> 00:09:38,990
The truth is that I was unable to remember anything from about three months before and after the incident.

101
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:43,650
But thanks to Yun, I am recovering my memories, little by little.

102
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:47,190
What memories have you recovered?

103
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:57,800
I remembered stabbing Kim Ian with a knife.

104
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,220
And?

105
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:04,860
Before Yun Yeong Gil died he told me a few things.

106
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,070
What did he tell you?

107
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:10,000
On that day, in the warehouse where Kim Ian and I were locked up

108
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,590
someone else was there.

109
00:10:12,590 --> 00:10:16,320
And that person is who may have killed Kim Ian.

110
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:20,590
And who is that person?

111
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:23,450
Our conductor.

112
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:29,900
Actually, Do Hun said something similar as well.

113
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,900
Yun did not kill Yun Yeong Gil.

114
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:39,720
Yun would never kill another person. Something is obviously very wrong.

115
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:44,450
I know that, too. You haven't visited him, have you?

116
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:50,420
He asked me to tell you something, but please hear it directly from him.

117
00:10:57,770 --> 00:11:01,660
Visitiation (Request)

118
00:11:09,060 --> 00:11:13,650
Name:  Jang Do Hun
Visitor: Hong Yi Yeong

119
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:27,330
Why did you come?

120
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,330
Gosh...

121
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:43,160
It's so weird to see you at a place like this.

122
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:48,300
You're not crying in there, are you?

123
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:58,170
I will bring you some clothes and food tomorrow morning.

124
00:11:58,170 --> 00:11:59,970
What do you want  to eat?

125
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:01,950
- Anything except your soup.
- Damn.

126
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:15,300
Don't visit me anymore. Even if you do, I won't come out to see you.

127
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:21,800
And don't do anything by yourself, it's dangerous. So wait until I'm released, okay?

128
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,700
Okay.

129
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:34,360
Do you know Professor Kang Myeong Seok of Sinyeong Music College, by any chance?

130
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:36,660
He is on the board of directors?

131
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:38,680
Yes.

132
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:44,070
He was a professor in the wind instrument section. Why?

133
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:48,320
How close were Conductor and Professor Kang Myeong Seok?

134
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,560
They seemed quite close, actually.

135
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:55,350
I heard that Professor Kang paid for Conductor's studies abroad.

136
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:58,090
Why?

137
00:12:58,090 --> 00:13:03,360
Nam Ju Wan and Professor Kang are somehow connected.

138
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,480
We have to be careful.

139
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,330
I will.

140
00:13:07,330 --> 00:13:10,930
I will be released soon, so don't worry.

141
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:15,240
Yes.

142
00:13:47,370 --> 00:13:49,630
Sinyeong College

143
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:04,170
SY Art Center

144
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:10,690
Hong Yi Yeong.

145
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:16,240
How is Jang Yun? You haven't heard anything?

146
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,640
No.

147
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:21,460
I heard that he was moved to the detention center. How long has it been?

148
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,440
It's been six days.

149
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,830
Based on the articles I read, there doesn't seem to be any evidence.

150
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:31,200
I don't understand how they got an arrest warrant.

151
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:36,640
It's not as if he's a flight risk. Have you visited him?

152
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:39,790
I go every day, but he won't see me.

153
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:46,670
In any case, do you plan to continue skipping our lessons?

154
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:51,080
I apologize.

155
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:58,160
I know that you are having a tough time, but I will only let you off for the rest of this week.

156
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:02,940
If you don't come to the lesson next week, there will be no more lessons.

157
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:57,900
♫  Shining day.

158
00:15:57,900 --> 00:16:03,710
♫  This day. Beautiful day.

159
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:24,780
♫ This thrilling day.  Beautiful day.  ♫

160
00:16:24,780 --> 00:16:29,560
♫ This day.  Shiny day. ♫

161
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:36,800
♫ seeing the brilliant you makes my heart tremble so much ♫

162
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:41,430
♫ my heart continues to beat ♫

163
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:45,000
♫ that brilliant ♫

164
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:49,350
♫ This day.  Beautiful day.♫

165
00:16:49,350 --> 00:16:51,610
Mr. Tone-Deaf

166
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:54,870
Hello.

167
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:56,430
Shall we eat together? It's been a long time.

168
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:59,700
♫ to be loving you ♫

169
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,810
♫ I'm gonna love with you ♫

170
00:17:11,540 --> 00:17:15,980
What happened? I heard you were moved to the detention center, so I thought I wouldn't be able to see you at all.

171
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:18,730
There is a complicated process called "review of legality for confinement."

172
00:17:18,730 --> 00:17:22,230
I was released by the court for lack of evidence. Investigation continues, of course.

173
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:26,190
In any case, what a good thing that you've been released.

174
00:17:26,190 --> 00:17:30,630
I wanted to go see someone today. You should come with me after we eat. You know this person, too.

175
00:17:30,630 --> 00:17:33,170
Someone I know?

176
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,200
- A ballpoint pen?
- Yes.

177
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:42,770
If it's a commemorative gift from Sinyeong Music College, then I probably have one too, somewhere.

178
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:47,700
But it's already a few years. It's when I was working on the faculty

179
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,000
Was it a gift only to the professors of Sinyeong Music College?

180
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,340
Yes, I think that it was. What about it?

181
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,460
Never mind.

182
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:02,730
- Are you healthy?
- Yes, look at me, very healthy.

183
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:09,700
Everyone was so worried after seeing the news. In any case, it's a relief that you've been released.

184
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,670
I will continue to be investigated.

185
00:18:11,670 --> 00:18:15,100
But since you haven't done anything, I'm sure it will work out soon.

186
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:19,660
After hearing that you'll be collaborating with Sinyeong Philharmonic, I was planning to contact you soon.

187
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:22,740
Of course, I never dreamed something like this would happen.

188
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:27,460
And you auditioned for Sinyeong Philharmonic?

189
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:30,900
- Yes.
- You did well.

190
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:35,240
To be honest, I was a little shocked to see you were using Ian's childhood name.

191
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:39,920
I didn't tell Manager Yun about it, assuming you had personal reasons for doing that.

192
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,560
There wasn't a big reason for it.

193
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:48,610
I thought that you were using his name because you were thinking of him after his death.

194
00:18:48,610 --> 00:18:51,690
And did you meet Yi Yeong at Sinyeong Philharmonic?

195
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:53,880
Yes, at Sinyeong Philharmonic.

196
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,220
Ian is one thing,

197
00:18:56,220 --> 00:19:00,310
but I made Yi Yeong suffer a lot of hardships, too.

198
00:19:00,310 --> 00:19:03,670
I forced her to become Ian's assistant.

199
00:19:03,670 --> 00:19:08,160
And that incident happened while they were on their way to my house.

200
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:10,660
It was just an accident.

201
00:19:10,660 --> 00:19:12,800
But still...

202
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:17,380
Coffee is here.

203
00:19:18,610 --> 00:19:21,630
She's still not dating anyone?

204
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:24,350
I thought she liked someone.

205
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:26,330
Huh, someone she liked?

206
00:19:26,330 --> 00:19:30,640
Ian was very concerned about that and confided in me many times.

207
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,380
What...

208
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:33,630
What ... confided in you?

209
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:37,540
Yes, he did. He really tortured me, when I am so old.

210
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:44,100
He loved Hong Yi Yeong so much, but he thought she liked someone else, so he couldn't even tell her.

211
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:47,850
Ian and Yi Yeong weren't dating?

212
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:53,300
Ian and Yi Yeong? I'm pretty sure they weren't.

213
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:59,320
Please take this. This is Professor's, and this is yours, Yun.

214
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,000
Oh, tastes bitter.

215
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:17,050
You seem like you're preoccupied, since a while ago.

216
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,990
No.

217
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,370
Go on in.

218
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:30,680
That thing Yun Yeong Gil hid.

219
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,830
Oh, yes?

220
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:35,860
I searched my uncle's flower shop for days, but I found nothing.

221
00:20:35,860 --> 00:20:40,420
I don't know what he hid, and whether he

222
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:44,850
really hid it, I have no idea. Until he died, he lied so easily.

223
00:20:44,850 --> 00:20:48,470
I understand, I will take care of the rest.

224
00:20:48,470 --> 00:20:50,330
Go in.

225
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,750
Auntie.

226
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:08,640
You should come inside if you've arrived. Let's go.

227
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:22,200
Thank you for working hard.

228
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:24,160
Hello.

229
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,280
What happened? Have you been released?

230
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,990
Yes, this afternoon.

231
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:33,140
What a relief. Everyone was worried.

232
00:21:34,020 --> 00:21:37,360
Oh, you didn't have to. We will enjoy eating this.

233
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:40,740
I stopped by earlier to organize my things

234
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:46,030
and lost some sheet music where I've made some important notes. I really must find it.

235
00:21:46,030 --> 00:21:50,980
I was so busy, I cannot remember where I might have lost it.

236
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:52,470
Is that right?

237
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:58,720
Can I check the video from about 2 p.m. to 4 p.m.?

238
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:02,800
Of course you can, that's not difficult at all. This way.

239
00:22:08,130 --> 00:22:12,620
From 2 p.m. to 4 p.m.

240
00:22:13,790 --> 00:22:17,310
Go ahead and watch. I have to go on patrol.

241
00:22:17,310 --> 00:22:19,190
Thank you.

242
00:22:35,230 --> 00:22:37,520
Father will be late today?

243
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:41,140
Friends are coming from Seosan, would he be early tonight?

244
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:43,930
He shouldn't drink too much.

245
00:22:46,590 --> 00:22:49,360
Why are you picking at your food?

246
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:54,900
Eat this too, don't just eat rice.

247
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,950
Oh, really.

248
00:23:01,230 --> 00:23:04,070
I am eating well, don't worry.

249
00:23:04,070 --> 00:23:07,510
No one would imagine how mistreated I am.

250
00:23:09,790 --> 00:23:11,470
Here.

251
00:23:16,980 --> 00:23:20,230
My mother used to listen to this song a lot.

252
00:23:26,830 --> 00:23:28,520
♫ When are you gonna come down? ♫

253
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:33,060
So I live always being prepared, making a "secret stash" that no one knows about.

254
00:23:33,060 --> 00:23:35,380
I hide it in a place that I like.

255
00:23:35,380 --> 00:23:37,270
If I happen to die, look for it.

256
00:23:37,270 --> 00:23:41,770
I may have left behind a gift for you.

257
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:51,180
I will go out for a bit.

258
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:55,950
Where are you going without finishing your dinner?

259
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:54,560
You got out sooner than I expected.

260
00:24:55,270 --> 00:24:57,290
I know you hoped I would be locked up longer.

261
00:24:57,290 --> 00:25:00,630
So now that you're out, have you gone back to stalking?

262
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:07,450
Why are you here?

263
00:25:07,450 --> 00:25:11,700
Enjoying the memory of having killed someone?

264
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:14,370
And what about you? Why follow me here?

265
00:25:14,370 --> 00:25:18,910
How did you manage to come up here on that day while avoiding the cameras?

266
00:25:18,910 --> 00:25:21,520
I wanted to test it out for myself.

267
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:27,130
It was so easy that I am dismayed. Please tell the security team that they should spend more money.

268
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:30,000
Sure, why not? See to your business, then.

269
00:25:33,110 --> 00:25:37,250
Did you think I would get scared and run away if you threw me into jail?

270
00:25:37,250 --> 00:25:42,540
Don't be mistaken. You took Yun Yeong Gil's bag from his storage, didn't you?

271
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:45,380
It was clearly captured on camera.

272
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:49,590
That bag contained evidence of murder, so that is why you went to get it, didn't you?!?

273
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:52,190
But you were curious about it, as well.

274
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:01,750
Welcome.

275
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:08,200
May I ask you a question?

276
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:12,010
I have some questions about someone who used to be a regular.

277
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:14,440
Yes, which one?

278
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:19,010
A man who recently passed away after an accident.

279
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:25,500
That man who died in some orchestra building? What was your question?

280
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:34,080
By any chance, has he left behind any personal items?

281
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:38,900
Wow, you really came? I was waiting for you.

282
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:45,600
That man who died, he said something strange that night.

283
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:50,000
- What did he say?
- That if a young woman came by

284
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:53,730
asking for an item that he left to my care,  I should give it to her.

285
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:57,300
- That it was a gift.
- A gift?

286
00:26:57,500 --> 00:27:00,630
Yes. Hold on.

287
00:27:04,430 --> 00:27:06,560
Welcome.

288
00:27:07,950 --> 00:27:14,920
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

289
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:27,650
Do you know Professor Kang Myeong Seok of Sinyeong Music College, by any chance?

290
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:30,250
He is on the board of directors?

291
00:27:34,210 --> 00:27:38,740
Nam Ju Wan and Professor Kang are somehow connected.

292
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:40,740
We have to be careful.

293
00:27:46,290 --> 00:27:51,030
♫ that exciting day, that day ♫

294
00:27:51,030 --> 00:27:54,790
♫ beautiful day ♫

295
00:27:56,260 --> 00:28:01,960
♫ my heart trembles so much, so much ♫

296
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,900
♫ it keeps trembling ♫

297
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:07,180
I Wanna Hear Your Song
Preview
♫ it keeps beating ♫

298
00:28:07,180 --> 00:28:09,150
That black car right behind us

299
00:28:09,150 --> 00:28:10,980
I feel it's been following us.

300
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:11,610
Yes.

301
00:28:11,610 --> 00:28:15,150
Fine, let's say I'm the criminal. There are no witnesses, and Hong Yi Yeong can't remember anything.

302
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:18,990
She already recalls that I was in that warehouse. It's only a matter of time.

303
00:28:18,990 --> 00:28:21,530
Because of the guilt of having stabbed your brother

304
00:28:21,530 --> 00:28:23,240
she lives having erased all her memories.

305
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:26,130
And then you showed up in front of her, treating her like a murderer and suspecting her.

306
00:28:26,130 --> 00:28:27,950
Jang Yun, it's your fault if she's like that now!

307
00:28:27,950 --> 00:28:29,600
I will find it.

308
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:36,380
Whatever you have hid, I will find it.  I'm going to personally watch you fall to the bottom.
